markdown: Chart 2 <::Line chart showing the relationship between "% Lysine added" and "gm gain / gm feed". Y-axis: gm gain / gm feed, ranging from 0.3 to 0.7. X-axis: % Lysine added, ranging from 0 to 0.7. Two data series are plotted: 1. "Corn-soy ration": Represented by a dashed horizontal line at approximately 0.7 gm gain / gm feed. 2. "Corn-safflower ration": Represented by a solid line with 'x' markers. The data points are: - (0, 0.4) - (0.1, 0.48) - (0.2, 0.57) - (0.3, 0.64) - (0.4, 0.69) - (0.5, 0.7) - (0.6, 0.7) - (0.7, 0.7) The "Corn-safflower ration" shows an increase in gm gain / gm feed as % Lysine added increases, eventually plateauing at 0.7, matching the "Corn-soy ration" level.: chart::> 434-64
